lead_paragraph: The State Department has failed to turn over government documents covering Hillary Rodham Clinton's tenure as secretary of state that The Associated Press and others requested under the U.S. Freedom of Information Act ahead of her presumptive presidential campaign. They include one request AP made four years ago and others pending for more than one year.

headline.main: Delays Plague Hillary Clinton's State Dept. Files
headline.print_headline: Delays Plague Hillary Clinton's State Dept. Files
